Issues.Body:
VMR is using P4 for dotnet and the SDK and gets support for  [? in L-values](https://github.com/dotnet/csharplang/blob/main/proposals/null-conditional-assignment.md) feature.
We have IDE0031 enabled as a warning and warnings are treated as errors. New P4 analyzers suggest changing code 
```C#
            if (pceltFetched is not null)
            {
                pceltFetched[0] = 0;
            }
```
to
```
pceltFetched?[0] = 0;
```

in VMR and build fails, but winforms repo build does not have these features yet. We'll update code to support the new features when we get P4.


_Originally posted by @NikolaMilosavljevic in https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/issues/13260#issuecomment-2785051966_
